diff --git a/docs/bandit-local.md b/docs/bandit-local.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..5e1a877
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/bandit-local.md
@@ -0,0 +1,45 @@
+# Local Bandit Scan
+
+This repository does not vendor Bandit. The local helper script creates an isolated Python virtual environment under `build/bandit/.venv`, installs Bandit there, and scans the ROS Python workspace under `ros2_ws/src`.
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+- `/usr/bin/python3` with `venv` support
+
+## Run the default local scan
+
+From the repo root:
+
+```bash
+bash ./scripts/run_bandit_local.sh
+```
+
+Artifacts are written to:
+
+- `build/bandit/.venv`
+- `build/bandit/report/bandit.txt`
+- `build/bandit/report/bandit.json`
+
+## Options
+
+```bash
+bash ./scripts/run_bandit_local.sh \
+  --target /tmp/python-src \
+  --venv-dir /tmp/agenticros-bandit/.venv \
+  --report-dir /tmp/agenticros-bandit/report
+```
+
+Supported flags:
+
+- `--target PATH` to scan a different directory
+- `--venv-dir PATH` to place the Python virtual environment elsewhere
+- `--report-dir PATH` to write reports elsewhere
+- `--no-clean` to keep any existing report files
+- `--skip-install` to reuse the current Bandit install in the venv
+- `--strict` to return a non-zero exit code when findings are reported
+
+## Notes
+
+- The default scan target is `ros2_ws/src`.
+- The helper only installs Bandit when it is missing from the selected virtual environment.
+- `build/` is gitignored in this repo, so the local Bandit environment and reports stay out of version control.
\ No newline at end of file
diff --git a/docs/coverity-local.md b/docs/coverity-local.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..8c2f5d8
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/coverity-local.md
@@ -0,0 +1,63 @@
+# Local Coverity Scan
+
+This repository does not vendor Coverity binaries. Install Synopsys Coverity Analysis locally first, then make sure `cov-build`, `cov-analyze`, and `cov-format-errors` are on your `PATH`.
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+- Coverity Analysis CLI installed locally
+- Node.js 20 or newer
+- pnpm 9 or newer
+- AgenticROS dependencies installed with `pnpm install`
+
+## Run the default local scan
+
+From the repo root:
+
+```bash
+pnpm coverity:local
+```
+
+The default mode uses build capture and wraps the repo's recursive build:
+
+```bash
+pnpm build
+```
+
+On the first run, the helper also generates `build/coverity/coverity_config.xml` with `cov-configure --typescript`, which covers the repo's TypeScript and JavaScript build inputs.
+
+Artifacts are written to:
+
+- `build/coverity/coverity_config.xml`
+- `build/coverity/idir`
+- `build/coverity/report/errors.json`
+- `build/coverity/report/html/index.html`
+
+## Run filesystem capture mode
+
+If your installed Coverity release supports `cov-build --fs-capture-search`, you can request filesystem capture explicitly:
+
+```bash
+pnpm coverity:local -- --mode fs
+```
+
+That mode searches these directories when supported by the local CLI:
+
+- `packages/`
+- `scripts/`
+- `examples/`
+- `ros2_ws/src/`
+
+## Custom output paths
+
+```bash
+bash ./scripts/run_coverity_local.sh \
+  --idir /tmp/agenticros-coverity/idir \
+  --report-dir /tmp/agenticros-coverity/report
+```
+
+## Notes
+
+- The script removes any previous `build/coverity` output unless you pass `--no-clean`.
+- The script fails fast with a clear error if the Coverity CLI is not installed.
+- Build capture is the default because it works across the validated local Coverity installation on this machine.
+- Filesystem capture remains optional and the script will reject it when the installed Coverity release does not expose `--fs-capture-search`.
\ No newline at end of file
diff --git a/docs/fuzz-local.md b/docs/fuzz-local.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..96dcd23
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/fuzz-local.md
@@ -0,0 +1,58 @@
+# Local Fuzz Testing
+
+This repository includes a local fuzz harness for high-risk ROS payload and config handling paths. The current targets span `packages/ros-camera`, `packages/core`, and `packages/agenticros`.
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+- Node.js 20 or newer
+- pnpm 9 or newer
+- AgenticROS dependencies installed with `pnpm install`
+
+## Run the default local fuzz pass
+
+From the repo root:
+
+```bash
+bash ./scripts/run_fuzz_local.sh
+```
+
+The helper script builds `@agenticros/core` and `@agenticros/ros-camera`, then runs a deterministic fuzz harness that exercises both built outputs and selected `packages/agenticros` source modules through `tsx`.
+
+Artifacts are written to:
+
+- `build/fuzz/report/summary.txt`
+- `build/fuzz/report/summary.json`
+
+## Options
+
+```bash
+bash ./scripts/run_fuzz_local.sh \
+  --iterations 5000 \
+  --seed 123456789 \
+  --report-dir /tmp/agenticros-fuzz
+```
+
+Supported flags:
+
+- `--iterations N` to change the iteration count per fuzz target
+- `--seed N` to reproduce a specific deterministic run
+- `--report-dir PATH` to write reports elsewhere
+- `--no-clean` to keep any existing report files
+- `--skip-build` to reuse existing package build artifacts
+
+## Scope
+
+The current fuzz harness exercises these surfaces with randomized but valid message-like inputs:
+
+- `coerceRosImageDataToBuffer` in `packages/ros-camera`
+- `cameraSnapshotFromPlainMessage` for both `Image` and `CompressedImage`
+- `fromRosMessage` image extraction in `packages/core/src/transport/local/conversion.ts`
+- `sampleDepthMeters`, `getDepthDistance`, and `getDepthSectors` in `packages/agenticros/src/depth.ts`
+- `readOpenClawConfig`, `writeAgenticROSConfig`, and `readAgenticROSConfigFromFile` in `packages/agenticros/src/config-file.ts`
+
+## Notes
+
+- The default run uses 1000 iterations per target.
+- The harness fails the run on the first unexpected exception or invariant violation for any target.
+- The validated broadened run fixed a real sync-delivery bug in `packages/agenticros/src/depth.ts`, where one-shot depth subscriptions could dereference `timer` before initialization if a transport invoked the message handler synchronously.
+- `build/` is gitignored in this repo, so local fuzz reports stay out of version control.
\ No newline at end of file
